    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment accepted at Medium assurance level. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required gradation. Test conditions factor (Gradation 2 achieved vs. Gradation 3 required) represents a single gap that is acknowledged and bounded by the conservative acceptance criteria applied to output comparison. All five validation comparisons satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10%. The FEA modeling framework is assessed as sufficiently credible to support the regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
